    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Testing Procedures",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "12-6-2REGULATION 12 MISCELLANEOUS STANDARDS OF PERFORMANCE ACID MIST FROM SULFURIC ACID PLANTS"
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "100",
      "section_title": "GENERAL",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "101",
      "section_title": "Description",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The purpose of this Rule is to limit the emission of sulfuric acid mist from sulfuric acid production units, the construction, modification or reconstruction of which commenced on or before August 17, 1971."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "200",
      "section_title": "DEFINITIONS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "201",
      "section_title": "Acid Mist",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Sulfuric acid mist as measured by test method outlined in 40 CFR 60.85."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "202",
      "section_title": "Sulfuric Acid Production Unit",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A plant producing sulfuric acid by the contact process by burning elemental sulfur, alkylation acid, hydrogen sulfide, organic sulfide and mercaptans or acid sludge, but does not include facilities where conversion to sulfuric acid is utilized primarily as a means of preventing emissions of sulfur dioxide or other sulfur compounds."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "300",
      "section_title": "STANDARDS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "301",
      "section_title": "Acid Mist",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "On or after December 6, 1978, a person shall not emit from a sulfuric acid production unit gases which contain acid mist expressed as H2SO4 in excess of"
      ],
      "subsections": [
        {
          "label": "0.15",
          "text": [
            "g per kg (0.3 lb/T) of acid produced."
          ],
          "subsections": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_id": "500",
      "section_title": "MONITORING AND RECORDS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "501",
      "section_title": "Production Rate and Hours of Operation",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person subject to this Rule shall record on a daily basis the production rate and hours of operation of the sulfuric acid production unit."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "600",
      "section_title": "MANUAL OF P ROCEDURES",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Testing Proced ures",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Emissions subject to the limitation of Section 12-6-301 shall be tested according to the method specified in Method 8 of Appendix A to 40 CFR 60."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    }
  ],
